>,<,>=,<=,==,!=

6.
= simply assigns the right value to the left variable.
== on the other handcomapres value and evealuates to True,False.

7.
A condition is used  in a flow control statement. It also controls the flow of code based on Boolean values.

8.
if spam == 10:
    print('eggs')
    if spam > 5:
        print('bacon')
    else:
        print('ham')
    print('spam')
    
if spam > 5:
        print('bacon')
        
else:
        print('ham')
        
        

9.
if spam == 1:
    print('Hello')
elif spam == 2:
    print('Howdy')
else:
    print('Greetings!')
    
