ctrl+C

11.
The break wil move out of a loop if a condition is met, continue on the other hand just skips the current condition and return to the begining of the loop.

12.

The range(10) call ranges from 0 up to 10, range(0, 10) tells the loop to start at 0, and range(0, 10, 1) tells the loop to increase the variable by 1 on each iteration.


13.
for i in range(1, 11):
    print(i)
    
    
i = 1
while i <= 10:
    print(i)
    i = i + 1
    
